My girlfriend's Scion constantly reminds me of old VWs. I always tell her it
was the modern VW bus when I drive it. Its not the toaster, but the little
station wagon scion She calls her Suzie. She looks like a suzie.

It is simplistic yet unique.
Extremely low cost of ownership.
Low maintenance
Relatively easy to fix
Reliable
Ridiculously economical; 38mpg highway ( the bus blushes in the driveway
next to it)
Tons of character
Fun to drive

Sounds like the same things that VW made a name with in the 60's.
I love her Scion.  I never thought I would like a modern car for the reasons
I love my buses. I was wrong


